<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-26T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/5–2645: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the United States Representative in
                                Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-26T12:00:00-04:00">May 26,
                                    1945—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>146. In order to forestall any eventual charge that we acted unilaterally
                            in a matter held to require joint action by the principal <pb facs="0239" n="227" xml:id="pg_227"/> Allies under the Yalta
                            formula, you should request General Crane to inform the ACC of
                            Dimitrov’s arrival at your residence and your prompt action in placing
                            the matter before the Bulgarian authorities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>